# Local development (default, no setup needed):
DATABASE_URL=file:./db/engineeros.db

# Production (Turso) — set these in your Vercel project's Environment Variables:
# DATABASE_URL=libsql://<your-db-name>-<your-org>.turso.io
# DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN=<token from `turso db tokens create <your-db-name>`>

# Pins all "today"/streak/date logic to this timezone regardless of what
# timezone the server process runs in (Vercel serverless functions default
# to UTC). Defaults to Asia/Kolkata if unset.
# APP_TIMEZONE=Asia/Kolkata

# --- Auth (multi-user) ---
# Real accounts live in the `users` table — there's no single admin
# password anymore. Registration requires a valid invite link (generated
# from Settings once logged in, or via the scripts below for first-time
# setup on a fresh database).
#
# First-time setup on a brand new database: `npm run db:push` seeds a demo
# account from these (falls back to owner@example.com / changeme-12345 if
# unset — change the password after logging in):
# OWNER_NAME=Your Name
# OWNER_EMAIL=you@example.com
# OWNER_PASSWORD=a-strong-password
#
# Migrating an existing single-user deployment onto this schema: run
# db/scripts/backfill-owner-account.ts (creates your user row) then
# db/scripts/backfill-existing-data-ownership.ts (assigns all existing
# rows to it) — see comments in those files for exact usage.
